        <h1>Scope & submission requirements</h1>

        <p>NeuroLibre submissions are expected to meet the following criteria:</p>

        <ul>
          <li> NeuroLibre submissions must be based on open source software and data (i.e., have an <a href="https://opensource.org/licenses/category">OSI-approved license)</a>.</li>
          <li> The execution of NeuroLibre submissions must also respect the limitations of the platform, both in terms of data size and execution duration - see our <a href="https://docs.neurolibre.org">technical documentation</a> for details.
        </ul>

        <p>
        Authors wishing to make a pre-submission enquiry are welcome to <%= link_to "open an issue", "https://github.com/#{Rails.application.settings["github"]}/issues/new?title=Pre-submission%20enquiry"%> on the <%= setting(:abbreviation) %> repository.
        </p>
      </div>

